children.name: deck a2
children.definition: deckmainly us/packuk a set of playing cards cỗ, xấp ( bài )
examples: a new deck of cards
a pack of cards
irene shuffled the deck.

children.name: card sharp x
children.definition: card sharp a person who earns money by playing cards dishonestly : kẻ chuyên ăn gian khi đánh bài

children.name: dealer x
children.definition: dealer the person who deals the cards in a game : người chia bài

children.name: shuffle x
children.definition: shuffle to mix a set of playing cards without seeing their values before beginning a game, so that their order is not known to any of the players : xáo bài
examples: is it my turn to shuffle?
shuffle the cards
justshuffle the cards.
it's your turn to shuffle the cards.
shuffle[c] when you mix a set of playing cards before giving them out
make sure you give the cards a good shuffle before you deal.

children.name: deal x
children.definition: deal to give playing cards to each of the players in a game : chia bài
examples: whose turn is it to deal?
deal them five cards each./ deal five cardstoeach of them.
deal out[m]
would you like to dealoutthe cards?
we have only a small amount of food and clothing to dealout toeach refugee.
deal[s] when sb deals (= sharesout) , especially playing cards
it's your deal (= turn to deal) .

children.name: cut x
children.definition: cut to divide a pack of cards into two: cắt bài
examples: who's going to cut the cards?
first cut the pack, and then deal the cards

children.name: pass x
children.definition: pass to choose not to play in a part of a card game or not to answer a question in a quiz : cho qua

children.name: play x
children.definition: play to choose a card, in a card game, from the ones you are holding and put it down on the table : đánh ra (một quân bài)
examples: she played the ace of spades.

children.name: raise x
children.definition: raise if you raise another player in a game of cards,you risk more money than that player has risked : đặt
examples: i'll raise you.
_ + two objects ]i'll raise you $50.

children.name: stick x
children.definition: stick in some card games, if you stick, you say that you do not want to be given any more cards.

children.name: trump x
children.definition: trump if you trump another player's card, you beat it with a card that belongs to the group of cards that has been chosen to have the highest value in the game you are playing: chặt, chặn (bằng lá bài chủ)

children.name: joker x
children.definition: joker a special playing card which can be given any value and is used in some card games instead of any other card

children.name: ace x
children.definition: ace one of the four playing cards with a single mark or spot, which have the highest or lowest value in many card games : quân át, quân xì;
examples: the ace of hearts/clubs/spades/diamonds

children.name: trump x
children.definition: trump/ trump card a card from the suit that has been chosen to have a higher value than the other suits in a particular game : lá bài chủ
examples: i played a trump.
luckily, idrewa trump.
trumps[p] the suit (= one of the four types of cards in a set ) chosen to have a higher value than the other suits in a particular card game :
diamonds are trumps.
hearts are trumps.

children.name: jack x
children.definition: jack/ knaveold use  a playing card with a picture of a man on it. it has a lower valuethan the cards showing a king or queen : bồi
examples: the jack of clubs

children.name: king x
children.definition: king a card with a picture of a king on it, used in games : lá bài k
examples: the king of hearts

children.name: queen x
children.definition: queen in a set of playing cards, a card with a picture of a queen on it. it is usually worth less than a king: quân đầm

children.name: card a2
children.definition: card/ playing card a small piece of thick stiff paper with numbers and signs or pictures on one side. there are 52 cards in a set.
examples: johnshuffled(= mixed up) the cards before hedealtthem (out).
pack/deck of cards(= a complete set of cards)
after dinner, ted got out apack/ us alsodeckof cards

children.name: club x
children.definition: club a playing card showing the black sign with three leaves nhép, chuồn
examples: clubs[u + sing/pl verb] one of the four suits in playing cards: quân rô trong bộ bài tây
the three of clubs

children.name: diamond x
children.definition: diamond a card, with a red diamond shape on it, which belongs to one of the foursuitsin a set of playing cards rô
examples: the six of diamonds

children.name: heart x
children.definition: heart a card, with a red heart shape on it, which belongs to one of the four suits in a set of playing cards con cơ

children.name: spade x
children.definition: spade a playing card with one or more black shapes like pointed leaves with short stems printed on it : con pích
examples: spadesone of the four suits in a set of playing cards quân pích
the ace/queenofspades

children.name: suit x
children.definition: suit any of the four types of card in a set of playing cards, each having a different shape printed on it : hoa
examples: the four suits in a pack of cards are hearts, spades, clubs and diamonds.

children.name: bridge x
children.definition: bridgenoungame bài brít
examples: [ u ] a card game for four players who play in pairs

children.name: rummy x
children.definition: rummynoun
examples: any of various card games in which two or more players try to collect cardswhich havethe same value or whose numbers follow an ordered series
gin rummynoun[ u ]bài rummy cho hai người chơi
a card game which is a type ofrummy

children.name: snap x
children.definition: snapnoungame lối chơi bài xnáp
examples: [ u ] a card game in which the players compete to call out the word 'snap' when they see two cards that have the same value
_a game of snap

children.name: patience x
children.definition: patiencenouncard game lối đánh bài paxiên (một người)
examples: uk(ussolitaire)a game played with cards by one person

children.name: canasta x
children.definition: canastanounlối chơi bài canaxta nam mỹ
examples: a card game for two to six people which is played with two sets of cards

children.name: solitaire x
children.definition: solitairenouncardslối đánh bài paxiên (một người)
examples: [ u ]us(ukpatience) a game played with cards by one person

children.name: poker x
children.definition: pokernoungame bài xì phé (đánh cược về giá trị của những quân bài họ đang giữ)
examples: [ u ] a game played with cards in which people try to win money from each other
strip pokernoun[ u ] cách chơi pôke trong đó người thua phải cởi quần áo
a card game in which players remove a piece of clothing each time they lose

children.name: whist x
children.definition: whistnoun đánh bài bài uýt
examples: a card game played between two pairs of players in which each side tries to win morecards than the other

children.name: hand x
children.definition: hand the set of cards which a player has in a game : bài
examples: youdealtme an appalling hand in that game.
